250 g Chorizo Sausage, uncased
¾ cup Parboiled Rice
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
28 g Crispy Shallots
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
½ tbsp Oil*

Once water is boiling, add rice and broth concentrate, then reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Thinly slice green onions.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chorizo, onions and peppers.
Cook, breaking up chorizo into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Add BBQ Seasoning and half the BBQ sauce.
Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min.

Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and green onions to the rice. Season with salt and fluff with a fork.
Divide rice between bowls. Top with chorizo mixture, cheese and crispy shallots.
Drizzle remaining BBQ sauce over top.

If you've opted to get chorizo, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef.**